        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 21 at 6:31PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 631 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 17
miles west of Colstrip, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Colstrip, Ashland, Brandenberg, Northern Cheyenne Indian
Reservation and Crow Indian Reservation.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
